<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870916-0112 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief:United Technologies Corp.</HL><DD> 09/16/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> UTX WNEWSAEROSPACE (ARO) </IN><TEXT>   United Technologies Corp. said it will combine several research and development teams working on space defense programs into a new business group.    The group, to be called the Strategic Defense Systems Division, will be based in Arlington, Va., and employ about 425 people. The new group will combine the company's Strategic Defense Program Office, based in Arlington, which does planning and research, and United Technologies Optical Systems, based in West Palm Beach, Fla., which is involved in such areas as laser technology.    United Technologies, which also makes helicopters, jet engines, elevators and air conditioners, said the combined operation will allow it to more effectively administer and market its space defense products.    Gordon H. Sigman Jr. has been named executive vice president and general manager of the new division. Mr. Sigman, 50 years old, had been vice president of the Strategic Defense Program Office.    The new unit will begin operating Oct. 1. </TEXT></DOC>